        "slug": "princeton-nlp/SWE-agent",
        "description": "Autonomous AI software engineering agent that resolves GitHub issues end-to-end.",
        "readmeExcerpt": "SWE-agent is an autonomous AI agent built for real-world software engineering. It reads a GitHub issue (or a local task description), explores the codebase, edits files, and submits a working patch — without human intervention.\n\n### 🎯 Use Cases\n- **Automatic GitHub Issue Resolution**: Triages bug reports and opens fully-formed PRs.\n- **Large-Scale Refactoring**: Applies repetitive code changes across an entire project safely.\n- **Legacy Code Analysis**: Reads, summarizes, and documents complex legacy systems.\n\n### ✨ Features\n- ACI (Agent-Computer Interface) for autonomous terminal command execution\n- File system navigation, code search, and deep static analysis\n- Native support for top-tier LLMs (Claude Sonnet, GPT-4o, and more)\n- State-of-the-art resolution rate on the SWE-bench benchmark\n\n### 👍 Pros\n- Solves problems end-to-end and produces actual pull requests with no human in the loop\n- Runs in an isolated Docker sandbox so it never touches your host environment\n- Academically rigorous — performance is verified on public benchmarks\n\n### 👎 Cons & Limitations\n- Initial Docker / environment setup is a bit involved\n- Struggles with high-level architectural decisions and can burn through API tokens quickly"
