        "description": "Pydantic-based library for getting structured, validated outputs from LLMs.",
        "readmeExcerpt": "Instructor patches the OpenAI (and many other) clients so that you can ask for structured outputs typed with Pydantic models. It handles retries, validation, and even streaming of partially-validated objects.\n\n### 🎯 Use Cases\n- **Structured Extraction**: Pull typed records out of free text.\n- **Function Calling 2.0**: Use Pydantic models directly as tool schemas.\n- **Reliable JSON**: Eliminate the \"please respond in JSON\" prompt-engineering headache.\n\n### ✨ Features\n- First-class Pydantic v2 support\n- Automatic retries on validation failure\n- Streaming of partial models as fields arrive\n- Works with OpenAI, Anthropic, Cohere, Ollama, and more\n\n### 👍 Pros\n- Makes structured outputs feel like a native Python feature\n- Eliminates a huge class of \"LLM returned invalid JSON\" bugs\n- Tiny API surface, easy to adopt incrementally\n\n### 👎 Cons & Limitations\n- Validation retries cost tokens\n- Only as expressive as your Pydantic model — complex schemas need careful design"
