        "description": "Constrained generation language for controlling LLM output structure and grammar.",
        "readmeExcerpt": "Guidance is a programming model for controlling LLMs at the token level. You interleave generation, control flow, and constraints — including regex and context-free grammars — to produce highly structured outputs.\n\n### 🎯 Use Cases\n- **Strict JSON & Schemas**: Generate output that always conforms to a grammar.\n- **Domain-Specific Languages**: Force the LLM to emit valid DSL code.\n- **Token-Efficient Prompts**: Reduce token usage with caching and structured generation.\n\n### ✨ Features\n- Grammar-constrained generation (regex, CFG)\n- Token healing and prompt caching for efficiency\n- Support for local models and hosted APIs\n- Composable program-style prompting\n\n### 👍 Pros\n- Eliminates entire categories of malformed output\n- Often faster and cheaper than retry-based structured output\n- Powerful when used with local open models\n\n### 👎 Cons & Limitations\n- Grammar features work best with open models that expose token logits\n- Learning curve is steep compared to simple prompting"
