        "readmeExcerpt": "HumanEval is OpenAI's seminal code-generation benchmark. It consists of 164 hand-written Python programming problems with unit tests, and is one of the most-cited benchmarks for LLM coding ability.\n\n### 🎯 Use Cases\n- **Model Comparison**: Compare coding capability across LLMs.\n- **Pass@k Reporting**: Standard metric used in papers and leaderboards.\n- **Fine-Tuning Validation**: Sanity-check coding fine-tunes.\n\n### ✨ Features\n- 164 problems with unit tests\n- `pass@k` evaluation harness\n- Lightweight and quick to run\n- Reference implementation in Python\n\n### 👍 Pros\n- De-facto standard for code generation benchmarks\n- Extremely lightweight to integrate\n- Widely cited — easy to compare against published numbers\n\n### 👎 Cons & Limitations\n- Saturated — top models score near the ceiling\n- Narrow scope (single-function Python tasks)"
