        "readmeExcerpt": "Reflexion is the reference implementation of the influential research paper of the same name. Agents reflect on their own failures, store the reflections in episodic memory, and use them to improve on subsequent attempts.\n\n### 🎯 Use Cases\n- **Self-Improving Agents**: Build agents that learn from their own mistakes.\n- **Research on Verbal RL**: Study verbal reinforcement learning for LLMs.\n- **Decision-Making Tasks**: Stronger results on long-horizon decision benchmarks.\n\n### ✨ Features\n- Reflexion loop: actor + evaluator + self-reflection\n- Episodic memory of past reflections\n- Implementations for coding, decision making, and reasoning tasks\n- Easy-to-read research code\n\n### 👍 Pros\n- Canonical implementation of a widely-cited technique\n- Demonstrates self-improvement without parameter updates\n- Useful template for building reflective agents\n\n### 👎 Cons & Limitations\n- Research-grade code, not a production framework\n- Limited active maintenance"
